transcript.text: Welcome to this tutorial on the Quick Design feature for the Front Store.
We are introducing this feature in our version 12.0.
Perfect for products that need only basic personalisation without the complexity of using all the Designer Studio tools to set it up for a specific product.
We have added a few new settings for admin to enable this flow.
Go to the Print Products section.
In the Admin panel, under the Products module, select the product, click Settings from the Action menu and in the General tab you will find the new Quick Design setting.
Let's enable this and check on the front store how it works.
Once enabled, customers will see three tabs on the front store, product options, front and back.
The number of tabs or pages depends on the template being personalized.
Customers can start by choosing product options and then move to a template where they can personalize images and text.
After customizing one page, they can go through the rest of the template pages, finishing with the option to go to check out.
All essential tools for personalisation, such as editing images and text are conveniently available on the template page, making customisation quick and effortless.
Customers can also browse other templates or switch to the full designer studio if they want more advanced options.
By default, the template shown for personalisation is based on sorting order, but you can prioritize a specific one by changing its order.
Additionally, if you want your customer to visit product templates first before the Quick Design page, then you can enable the template selection before product landing page setting and that's it.
With these few settings, you can offer the Quick Design feature to the customers, making the product customization and order journey faster and easier, creating a smooth and enjoyable experience.
We look forward to seeing how these updates help enhance your business operations.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
